annotation.TEXT: This is apparently the top of this No-Yoshi barrier.
Ah, the fake coin room. Let's see what happens if I fly over the teleport here...
I just discovered something while replaying this level-- You can slide-kill the boo beams!
I know I just saw a moon there!
Nope, I can't get in. Well, then...
Gulp!
Now, let's see what's to the right of the goal sphere...
Oh, by the way, don't worry about the red coins too much. They can drop your coin total down to zero, but that's it.
Ha! With my green P-switch, I no longer need to fear the red munchers here!
Red moon=Prinny reincarnation, but nothing that Mario can use, dood.
The wind can also allow you to build running speed in place, which seems weird, but whatever!
However, be very careful, as the trail they leave behind will hurt you even if you're sliding.
...Huh? (Reading my last annotation) Do "bounce on" and "bounce off" have the same meaning or something? Because they both sound right... Oh yeah, and pit=death here.
Well, let's check out the area to the right before abandoning Yoshi...
Red munchers=munchers, red koopa=spiny.
Well, I can bounce on the ghost to get back... Oh! Maybe in the "non-insane" version of this room, you can bounce off the other ghosts that are normally there...
What if I were to... Oh, wait. Yoshi can't get into the door again... D'oh!
Am I seriously expecting to find anything of interest to the right of these places?
YEAHHH!!! Also, the red coins that have changed to blocks are still collectable, and still decrease your coin counter like usual.
Yeah, I'm perfectly capable of going over the top, which makes dodging the goal sphere infinitely easier!
Now, I want to stay on the lower path, because there isn't really much of interest I can do in the vertical area.
However, this part can also be used as a minor shortcut, either by flying, or tanking a hit.
Darn it, Yoshi! Why! Can't! You! Get! In! The! Darned! Door!?
Huh?!
They won't kill you or anything, and no matter how many red coins you get while at zero, the first green coin you get will bring you back to 1.
Yep, they become shells when munched on as well!
Hi, Yoshi!
Yeouch! That's okay! I'm still flying!
Yep, I was right about the "probably empty" part.
(Abandons Yoshi mid-flight...)
Yoshi's glitchy tongue grabs the key! ...Oh, yeah. There's a locked door sprite... Yoshi's never going to get through that...
Still nothing, but what about one of the levels that ends with a MOON? (It's easier to dodge the goal sphere when you can get running speed.)
Okay, nothing of interest up here (I'm guessing the midpoint room is just below). Let's cut to a later portion of the level now...
Which means all that effort I just went through was a complete waste! (Insert Duffman's "OHHH, YEEEAAAHHH!!!" here.)
Thank you, Yoshi! But your usefulness is in another castle!
Now, before I end this, I want to check out one thing I missed in this room...
Now, up and to the left of here is the part that I didn't explore before.
Let this be a lesson: When you're going insane, don't do something crazy!
Ah! This'll do!
NOOOOOOOO!!!!! I can't get Yoshi into the door!
Red ground=munchers, and bottomless pit=bottomless pit...
Exploring to the right again, we find...
Well, bye, Yoshi!
Then, you can use the other guy to get back. Also, the screen stops scrolling shortly after the moon, as it should do.
Well, I guess I don't need Yoshi for fooling around during the "insanity" rooms...
Yes, there's a moon across that large pit! I wonder how you're normally supposed to reach it...
It's a shame, too. I really wanted to see if Yoshi could eat the giant eye boss...
Green moon=MOOOOOONNN!!! This one requires the red P-switch to collect.
Now, I want to take both of them with me, so it's time to double grab!
Will this level suck, or blow?

Yeah, I had to reset and replay a different level, so that I could enter Yoshi n Berry with a cape. (Yoshi n Berry was already cleared on the other file to get Yoshi, which is why I couldn't reenter it.)
Okay, I'm going to do one last "fly over a teleport in an insanity room" thing, then I'm done with this level.
Okay, how about the "insanity" version of this dark room? What is beyond the teleport?
I'll stand on the barrier, of course!
Moon.
The cape can offer some interesting advantages in windy areas if you know what you're doing.
Wheeeeee!!!
Yeah, in the normal version of this room, you can hitch a ride on a ghost moving to the right, and that's how you're probably supposed to reach the moon!
And of course, the wind can still throw you around while you're flying, so be careful.
And of course, there's still nothing of interest in this vast region...
Honestly, it's mostly the same familiar room, but with no door at the end, and death if I fall into a pit. You know, the usual.
MOOOOOOOOONNNNN!!!!!!

Okay, it's finally time to revisit Source of Variety! Now, what I did here was, cleared one level, got two capes here, then died in a pit so I'd be small with a cape in reserve, then I cleared three more levels including Yoshi n Berry.
Oh, yeah. These spiders-- They're just like various other moving hazards seen throughout the hack. Immune to almost everything, except cape spinning.
Uh, oh. Mario became a lemming again. (Quick, give him an umbrella! Too late...)
So let's see... Are Loss of Sanity's goombas...
Zip. Zilch. Nada. An integer that's less than one.
An unusual amount of open airspace within this mansion!
Well, I think that'll about do it. I hope you've enjoyed watching me play through EVW! I guess I'll just play the rest of the level now...

So, while Mario's exploring yet another empty region, let's talk about the weather. I hear Connecticut's supposed to get some snow in certain places tonight. Brrr... It feels too early in the year for that!
I did not TAS that stunt! That happened totally by accident!
(...I'm gonna lose my sanity soon if this computer doesn't stop BSoD-ing me...) Oh, hello everyone, and welcome back to the final episode of Extreme Variety World!
Now let's see if I can find a decent takeoff spot after hitting the wind block...
Crazy Through!
Bye, Yoshi!
Well, the sprites are present starting immediately after the teleport...
Okay, there's one more thing I can try right here. Let's fly over the top!
Well, the screen stops scrolling at a reasonable place here, although there's still the usual cutoff with the ground.
Okay, up next is the final regular level, Yoshi n Berry... Wait, what's going on? I can't enter the level! One moment please.
(Finds nothing of interest, falls to death, and reloads earlier savestate...)
Ow! What the heck did I hit? I think there's a black berry offscreen here! That's kind of unfair...
Green spiny=goomba.
Is there any chance the red door is different? (Although, I'll have to use my cape to reach it...)
Red P-switch=Blue P-switch, Green P-switch=Silver P-switch.
Yoshi's feet have innate sharp object immunity.
Shortcut! (Actually, this'll probably work if you're at least super, and willing to take a hit.)
Oops! Oh, no! Kaizo trap! Bye, Mario!
Let's try that in a more intelligent way, after I get a spare cape for no reason.
A bit later on in the level, I can fly to the right from this door, where I find...
The screen actually does stop scrolling at a reasonable spot here.
Alright, let's finish this level...
Oh, wow! You can get Yoshi into the sprite doors by pressing up as you land on him!
And, as is the norm for this game, I can easily get another moon!
Now there's another vast (probably empty) region to the right of this area. I could try searching for a decent takeoff spot, or...
And past the non-existent door, there's the same open airspace as before. (Hey, that rhymes!)
...I could "hyper avoid" my way over there!
Red vines=munchers, green munchers=safe ground, red lava=lava, green lava=water. Makes perfect sense!
However, that knowledge is totally worthless on the normal doors that just don't like Yoshi...
Caution: Turbulence ahead. Please fasten safety belts.
What?! OH, NOOO!!!
Uh, oh! Invisible anti-Yoshi barrier! Whatever shall I do?
Hopefully, this'll let me get Yoshi into a door at the beginning...
By the way, this is where I just flew to the right from, before touching the wind block.
